                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/7–1240: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-12T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 12, 1940—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>188. Department’s telegram dated July 11, 4 p.m.<note n="5" xml:id="d85fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_19">p. 19</ref>.</note>
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs in my presence telephoned Minister of War. Both of
                    them are entirely agreeable to renewing talks early August.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Braden</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
